<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-12-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="385" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d385">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tower</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-12-19"><hi rend="italic">December 19,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Tower reports that, in accordance with the Department’s cabled
                            instructions, he has communicated to the German Government the
                            Venezuelan proposition that the United States minister at Caracas be
                            empowered to enter into negotiations on the part of Venezuela to settle
                            the present difficulties, and has asked whether Germany is disposed to
                            assent thereto.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>